{
  "schema_version": "1.0",
  "name": "Wheatstone Bridge with NTC Thermistor",
  "description": "Classic Wheatstone bridge for precision resistance measurement. RT1 (NTC thermistor) is the unknown. R1=R2=R3 at balance point. Bridge output drives op-amp differential amplifier. Null detector or meter reads bridge imbalance proportional to temperature.",
  "notes": "At balance: RT1/R3 = R2/R1. With matched R1=R2=R3=10kΩ, bridge nulls at RT1=10kΩ (25°C for typical NTC). Sensitivity: ~1mV/°C with 5V supply. U1 (op-amp) amplifies differential output. RV1 sets balance point offset. Used in temperature measurement, strain gauges, load cells.",
